1) What is an Error Boundary?
An Error Boundary is a React component that catches errors in other components so the whole app does not crash.
It shows a simple error message instead of breaking the entire page.
It is useful because it keeps the app working and makes errors easier to handle.



2) Methods in an Error Boundary

getDerivedStateFromError(error)
Used to update the state when an error happens.
It tells React to show an error message instead of the broken component.

componentDidCatch(error, info)
Used to get information about the error and log it (for example, in the console).
Helps developers find and fix the problem.

reset()
Used to clear the error and try to render the component again.
Usually connected to a button like “Try again”.